name=Bandits Performance Override
id=BanditsPerformanceOverride
description=Performance override for the Bandits (V2) framework on B42, aimed at dense human-NPC scenes like Bandits: Week One (which can drop to ~8 FPS). Overrides the core combat loop (BanditUpdate.lua) and rewrites its per-tick, all-pairs proximity / line-of-sight scan (ManageCombat) -- the O(N^2) cost behind the low framerate. Four changes: (1) a count-based throttle so peaceful, non-hostile NPCs scan a few times per second instead of every update, while anyone in combat or flagged hostile stays fully responsive; (2) a shooter-safe distance gate that spares melee NPCs the expensive line-of-sight checks on far targets while ranged NPCs keep full engagement range; (3) de-duplicated flee handling (no redundant second full-cell pass); and (4) a coarse spatial grid so each scan only checks nearby NPCs instead of the whole cell -- turning the cost from O(N^2) into roughly O(local density). Measured from 8 FPS at ~100 bandits to smooth at ~300. Loads after Bandits (require=Bandits2) and replaces its combat loop via file shadowing; pinned to Bandits 42.18 -- re-sync when the core mod updates.
modversion=0.2.0
require=Bandits2
